In order to verify the effect of Fmoc-Ala-OH molecule on the trap state density of perovskite films, space charge limited current (SCLC) measurement in the dark based on the electron-only device was implemented, as shown in Fig. 5c. The sample structure was FTO/PCBM/perovskite film/PCBM/Ag. The low bias section means ohmic reply, and the image shows an inflection point where the current increases rapidly, which is called the defect trap filling voltage (VTFL).39 The value of VTFL is directly related to the density of defect states (nt) in the device (VTFL=entL22εε0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
